              <div class="example" id="base-path-and-path">
                  <div class="col-xs-11 col-sm-11 col-md-11">
                      <h2><a href="./">Ballerina by Example</a>: Base Path and Path</h2>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-xs-1 col-sm-1 col-md-1">
                      <a href="./" class="cBackButton"><img src="http://b.content.wso2.com/sites/all/ballerina/backbutton.svg"/></a>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12">

                      

                      <table>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>Ballerina support writing RESTFul services according to JAX-RS specification. BasePath,
 Path and HTTP verb annotations such as POST, GET, etc can be used to
 constrain your service in RESTful manner.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nx">ballerina</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">net</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">http</span><span class="p">;</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>BasePath attribute associates a path to the service.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre><span class="nd">@http:config {</span><span class="nx">basePath</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="s">&quot;/foo&quot;</span><span class="p">}</span>
<span class="kd">service</span><span class="p">&lt;</span><span class="nx">http</span><span class="p">&gt;</span> <span class="nx">echo</span> <span class="p">{</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>Post annotation constrains the resource only to accept post requests. Similarly, for each HTTP verb there are different annotations.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre>    <span class="nd">@http:POST {</span><span class="p">}</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>Path annotation associates a sub-path to resource.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre>    <span class="nd">@http:Path {</span><span class="nx">value</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="s">&quot;/bar&quot;</span><span class="p">}</span>
    <span class="kd">resource</span> <span class="nx">echo</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="kt">message</span> <span class="nx">m</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="p">{</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>A util method that can convert the request to a response.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code leading">
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre>        <span class="nx">http</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nx">convertToResponse</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">m</span><span class="p">);</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  <p>Send back the response to the client.</p>

                              </td>
                              <td class="code">
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre>        <span class="nx">reply</span> <span class="nx">m</span><span class="p">;</span>
    <span class="p">}</span>
<span class="p">}</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                      </table>


                      

                      <table>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  
                              </td>
                              <td class="code">
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre><span class="gp">$</span> ballerina run service base-path-and-path.bal
<span class="go">ballerina: deploying service(s) in &#39;.../base-path-and-path.bal&#39;</span>
<span class="go">ballerina: started server connector http-9090</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                      </table>


                      

                      <table>
                          
                          <tr>
                              <td class="docs">
                                  
                              </td>
                              <td class="code">
                                  <div class="highlight"><pre><span class="gp">$</span> curl http://localhost:9090/foo/bar -d <span class="o">{</span><span class="se">\&quot;</span>hello<span class="se">\&quot;</span>: <span class="se">\&quot;</span>world<span class="se">\&quot;</span><span class="o">}</span> -H <span class="s2">&quot;Content-Type: application/json&quot;</span>
<span class="go">{&quot;hello&quot;: &quot;world&quot;}</span>
</pre></div>

                              </td>
                          </tr>
                          
                      </table>


                      
                      
